WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.800
Happy to announce our arrival at New York City.

00:02.800 --> 00:05.600
The train will be stopping in five minutes.

00:05.600 --> 00:08.000
Please check to be sure you have your belongings

00:08.000 --> 00:10.240
and have a good stay in the big apple.

00:10.240 --> 00:11.400
Thank you.

00:11.400 --> 00:13.640
Well, here we are.

00:13.640 --> 00:16.240
With so nice meeting you, Mr. Stewart.

00:16.240 --> 00:19.480
And nice meeting you too, Mrs. Dober.

00:19.480 --> 00:20.720
Please look us up.

00:20.720 --> 00:25.120
We're in the phone book, Dr. Philip Stewart, in Riverdale.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.120
Your son.

00:26.120 --> 00:28.120
That's right.

00:28.120 --> 00:31.200
But have a good time in New York.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.640
And don't be so independent.

00:33.640 --> 00:36.120
You're very lucky to have a caring family.

00:36.120 --> 00:37.120
OK.

00:48.840 --> 00:50.320
When can we go fishing?

00:50.320 --> 00:53.640
Robbie, we'll go fishing soon.

00:53.640 --> 00:55.680
I'm going to take your dad with us.

00:55.680 --> 00:57.640
I'm ready, Grandpa.

00:57.640 --> 00:59.400
You name the day.

00:59.400 --> 01:01.160
That's a great idea, Grandpa.

01:01.160 --> 01:03.440
Philip needs a day off.

01:03.440 --> 01:04.720
Let's give him our presence.

01:04.720 --> 01:05.360
Now.

01:05.360 --> 01:06.840
Good idea.

01:06.840 --> 01:08.720
Present for me.

01:12.320 --> 01:14.640
From me and Marilyn.

01:14.640 --> 01:16.360
And this one's from me.

01:16.360 --> 01:18.000
Looked all over the house to find it.

01:25.680 --> 01:30.680
Oh.

01:30.680 --> 01:32.680
This shirt.

01:32.680 --> 01:40.680
These are terrific pictures.

01:40.680 --> 01:46.680
This one really brings back memories.

01:46.680 --> 01:49.680
You remember that day, Robbie?

01:49.680 --> 01:50.680
He sure do.

01:50.680 --> 01:51.680
It was fun.

01:51.680 --> 01:52.680
Uh-oh.

01:52.680 --> 01:59.680
I'm sorry Susan didn't hear.

01:59.680 --> 02:03.680
I miss her very much.

02:03.680 --> 02:06.680
She feels bad too, Grandpa.

02:06.680 --> 02:08.680
She called to say the plane was delayed.

02:08.680 --> 02:10.680
You know airports.

02:10.680 --> 02:13.680
I can't wait to see her.

02:13.680 --> 02:18.680
She looks just like Grandma at that age.

02:18.680 --> 02:23.680
I'd better unpack.

02:23.680 --> 02:28.680
I started traveling 24 hours ago.

02:28.680 --> 02:32.680
Not so young anymore.

02:32.680 --> 02:35.680
Don't you want something to eat?

02:35.680 --> 02:37.680
No, thanks.

02:37.680 --> 02:40.680
After a good night's sleep, I'll enjoy breakfast even more.

02:40.680 --> 02:42.680
Well, come on, Dad.

02:42.680 --> 02:44.680
Ellen and I will take you to your room.

02:44.680 --> 02:46.680
I'm so glad you're here, Grandpa.

02:46.680 --> 02:47.680
Hi.

02:47.680 --> 02:48.680
Good night, Grandpa.

02:48.680 --> 02:49.680
Hey.

02:49.680 --> 02:50.680
Pleasant dreams.

02:50.680 --> 02:51.680
Mm.

02:51.680 --> 02:56.680
All right.

02:56.680 --> 02:57.680
All right.

02:57.680 --> 03:02.680
Good.

03:02.680 --> 03:06.680
Oh.

03:06.680 --> 03:08.680
Do you have the key to the trunk?

03:08.680 --> 03:11.680
I have the key, but it doesn't work.

03:11.680 --> 03:18.680
I sent the wrong key.

03:18.680 --> 03:35.680
I have something for you.

03:35.680 --> 03:38.680
I made it myself.

03:38.680 --> 03:41.680
I think you'll enjoy it.

03:41.680 --> 03:44.680
I researched it for over a year.

03:44.680 --> 03:49.680
It's our family tree.

03:49.680 --> 03:51.680
Oh, good.

03:51.680 --> 03:52.680
Grandpa.

03:52.680 --> 03:54.680
How exciting.

03:54.680 --> 03:56.680
Fabulous.

03:56.680 --> 04:00.680
But I didn't know that your grandfather was born in Germany.

04:00.680 --> 04:04.680
Lots of interesting information about our family.

04:04.680 --> 04:07.680
A gift from me.

04:07.680 --> 04:10.680
Thank you so much.

04:10.680 --> 04:11.680
Grandpa.

04:11.680 --> 04:13.680
Grandpa.

04:13.680 --> 04:16.680
I'm so happy to see you.

04:16.680 --> 04:20.680
Oh, he looked so beautiful, Susan.

04:20.680 --> 04:22.680
My granddaughter.

04:22.680 --> 04:24.680
Like I always said.

04:24.680 --> 04:27.680
You look just like Grandma.

04:27.680 --> 04:31.680
I think you're going to be very happy here with us.

04:31.680 --> 04:34.680
I know you, will.

04:34.680 --> 04:38.680
I don't feel alone anymore.

